<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4054> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4054" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "C. Iulius Caesar succeeded L. Cornelius Merula. Vell. 2.20.3; App. BC 1.65, and 74; Augustiii. CD 3.27. See above, Consul Suffectus." ;
	dprr:hasID 4054 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4003> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4003" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Flamen Dialis, who was elected colleague of Octavius (see above). He abdicated his office when the Marians won, and when placed on trial abdicated his priesthood and committed suicide (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 54f., 129, 482f.; Diod. 38.3; Val. Max. 9.12.5; Vell. 2.20.3, and 22.2; Tac. Ann. 3.58; Plut. Mar. 41.1; 45.2; App. BC 1.65- 66; 70; 74; Flor. 2.9.16; Dio 30-35, fr. 102.11 a; 54.36. 1; Augustin. CD 3.27). See Flamen Dialis." ;
	dprr:hasID 4003 .
